2402:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c **** /**
2403:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @brief  Enter ADC deep-power-down mode
2404:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @note   This mode is achieved in setting DEEPPWD bit and allows to save power
2405:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         in reducing leakage currents. It is particularly interesting before
2406:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         entering stop modes.
2407:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @note   Setting DEEPPWD automatically clears ADVREGEN bit and disables the
2408:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         ADC voltage regulator. This means that this API encompasses
2409:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         HAL_ADCEx_DisableVoltageRegulator(). Additionally, the internal
2410:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         calibration is lost.
2411:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @note   To exit the ADC deep-power-down mode, the user is expected to
2412:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         resort to HAL_ADC_Init() API as well as to relaunch a calibration
2413:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         with HAL_ADCEx_Calibration_Start() API or to re-apply a previously
2414:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         saved calibration factor.
2415:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @param hadc ADC handle
2416:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @retval HAL status
2417:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   */
2418:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_adc_ex.c **** HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_ADCEx_EnterADCDeepPowerDownMode(ADC_HandleTypeDef *hadc)
